===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[agitate]] [[rapid]]ly and [[repetitive]]ly, or to [[stir]] with a [[row]]ing or [[rock]]ing motion; generally applies to [[liquid]]s, notably [[cream]].
#: {{ux|en|Now the cream is '''churned''' to make butter.}}
#: {{ux|en|no-'''churn''' ice cream}}
#* {{RQ:Addison Meta}}
#*: {{quote|en|'''Churned''' in his teeth, the foamy venom rose.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive|figuratively}} To [[produce]] [[excessive]] and sometimes [[undesirable]] or [[unproductive]] [[activity]] or [[motion]].
#* {{quote-journal|en|year=2012|author=John Branch|title=Snow Fall: The Avalanche at Tunnel Creek|newspaper={{w|New York Times}}| url=http://www.nytimes.com/projects/2012/snow-fall/?smid=fb-nytimes&WT.z_sma=SP_SNT_20130415#/?part=tunnel-creek| passage=The slope of the terrain, shaped like a funnel, squeezed the growing swell of '''churning''' snow into a steep, twisting gorge.}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To move rapidly and repetitively with a rocking motion; to [[tumble]], [[mix]] or [[shake]].
#: {{ux|en|I was so nervous that my stomach was '''churning'''.}}
# {{lb|en|of a customer}} To stop using a company's product or service.
# {{lb|en|informal|travel|aviation}} To repeatedly [[cancel]] and [[rebook]] a reservation in order to refresh ticket time limits or other [[fare]] rule restrictions.
# {{lb|en|US|informal|finance|travel}} To continually sign up for new [[credit card]]s in order to earn signup bonuses, [[airline mile]]s, and other benefits.
# {{lb|en|finance}} To carry out [[wash sale]]s in order to make the [[market]] appear more [[active]] than it really is.

